---
layout: layouts/base.njk
title: For Musicians
description: "Send an 8 bar slice of stems from one of your songs and get your own spot in the SYNTHERION cosmos: your name, album art, and Spotify in-game, plus a video showcasing your work."
permalink: /for-musicians/
ogImage: /assets/og/for-musicians-v2.jpg
---

{% include "partials/site-header.njk" %}

<header class="musicians-hero">
  {% if site.hero.videoUrl %}
  <video class="musicians-hero__video" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster="{{ site.hero.posterUrl }}">
    {% if site.hero.mobileVideoUrl %}
    <source src="{{ site.hero.mobileVideoUrl }}" type="video/mp4" media="(max-width: 720px) and (orientation: portrait)">
    {% endif %}
    <source src="{{ site.hero.videoUrl }}" type="video/mp4">
  </video>
  {% endif %}
  <div class="musicians-hero__vignette" aria-hidden="true"></div>

  <div class="musicians-hero__content">
    <p class="musicians-hero__eyebrow">For Musicians</p>
    <h1 class="visually-hidden">For Musicians</h1>
    <div class="musicians-pitch-box">
      <p class="musicians-pitch-box__lead">
        Get your music in the game.
      </p>
      <p class="musicians-pitch-box__sub">
        Syntherion is a unique way to reach new listeners and send them directly to your work.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</header>

<main class="musicians-page">

  <section class="section musicians-intro">
    <h2 class="section__heading musicians-intro__heading">How it works</h2>
    <div class="musicians-intro__grid">
      <div class="musicians-intro__card">
        <span class="musicians-intro__eyebrow">The game</span>
        <p>A pew-pew roguelite where all levels sync to synthwave and darksynth music.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="musicians-intro__card">
        <span class="musicians-intro__eyebrow">How to get involved</span>
        <p>Join the <a href="{{ site.social.discordInvite }}" rel="noopener">Discord</a> and submit a link to your Spotify for review.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="musicians-intro__card">
        <span class="musicians-intro__eyebrow">What you get</span>
        <p>Your name, art, and Spotify link in-game. Plus a flashy video showcasing your music.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section musicians-trailer-link">
    <p><a href="/#trailer">Watch the trailer to see music in action →</a></p>
  </section>

  <section class="section musicians-showcase">
    <h2 class="section__heading">What players see</h2>
    <div class="musicians-showcase__media">
      <video autoplay muted loop playsinline preload="metadata" aria-hidden="true">
        <source src="/assets/artist-promotion/featured_artist_map.mp4" type="video/mp4">
      </video>
    </div>
    <p class="musicians-showcase__caption">
      Your track gets its own spot in the cosmos. Players who land on it meet a panel with your name, album art, song title, and a one-tap link to your Spotify.
    </p>
    <p class="musicians-footage-note">Early development footage. Visuals will evolve.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="section musicians-social">
    <div class="musicians-social__grid">
      <div class="musicians-social__media">
        <video autoplay muted loop playsinline preload="metadata" aria-hidden="true">
          <source src="/assets/artist-promotion/artist_social_short.mp4" type="video/mp4">
        </video>
      </div>
      <div class="musicians-social__body">
        <h2 class="section__heading musicians-social__heading">What you'll receive</h2>
        <p>A post showcasing your work in-game, plus your own copy of the video if you would like to post direct from your own social accounts.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section musicians-cta">
    <h2 class="section__heading">Interested?</h2>
    <a class="btn--discord" href="{{ site.social.discordInvite }}" rel="noopener">Find Tim on the Discord →</a>
  </section>

  <section class="section musicians-tech">
    <h2 class="section__heading musicians-tech__heading">Technical details</h2>
    <ul class="musicians-tech__list">
      <li>An 8 bar slice of your own music.</li>
      <li>Stems, delivered as a ZIP.</li>
      <li>One isolated instrument per stem.</li>
      {# ASK TIM: under the new "levels sync to music" system, does each stem still become its own weapon? The old copy read "One isolated instrument per stem (each becomes its own weapon, so a bounced mix won't work)." I dropped the parenthetical since the mechanic framing changed — restore or reword if it still holds. #}
      <li>44.1 kHz WAV.</li>
      <li>Submit as many stems as you'd like.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

</main>
